sections.text:
All persons have the inherent and inalienable right to enjoy and defend their lives and liberties;
to acquire, possess and protect property; to worship according to the dictates of their consciences;
to assemble peaceably, protest against wrongs, and petition for redress of grievances; to
communicate freely their thoughts and opinions, being responsible for the abuse of that right.

The Legislature shall provide for the establishment and maintenance of the state's education
systems including: (a) a public education system, which shall be open to all children of the state;
and (b) a higher education system. Both systems shall be free from sectarian control.
